714974f-a.title: Manhattan: 105th Street (East) - 2nd Avenue
714974f-a.text:
A rear view of 250 East 105th Street, south side, west of Second Ave.
Building shown is the Union Settlement AptS., a slum clearance project.
August 12, 1929.
Ewing Galloway.

707960f-a.title: Manhattan: 2nd Avenue - 105th Street (East)
707960f-a.text:
Second Avenue, south from East 105th Street, as photographed
from the uptown "El" platform.
Shown on the center track is an express train that runs south-
ward in the morning and northward in the afternoon.
June 7, 1940
Views 1,2
P. L. Sperr
